  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Reference Architectures&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    One of the key elements necessary for successfully&amp;nbsp;describing the context of an asset is to identify where within&#xD;
    an architecture an asset should be used. A reference architecture identifies an architectural pattern, typically&#xD;
    in&amp;nbsp;a set of layers. The assets should be classified to align with these layers. Classifying the assets this way&#xD;
    allows the asset consumer to navigate the repository using the reference architecture as the way to discover the&#xD;
    assets.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The image below introduces a sample reference architecture. The assets to the right are classified according to these&#xD;
    layers.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img height=&quot;243&quot;&#xD;
    alt=&quot;This image shows a reference architecture with the assets classified according to the architectural layers&quot;&#xD;
    src=&quot;./resources/assets_align_with_architecture.gif&quot; width=&quot;492&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
